It was seen as a huge blow for John Major's government and led to a surge for the Lib Dems in Hampshire who went on to win Portsmouth, South, Winchester and Christchurch. Paddy Ashdown promoted Chidgey to transport spokesman. He was praised for fighting for rail travellers. In the 1997 general election, he held Eastleigh as New Labour swept to power. He was made a life peer in 2005, spending his first two years in the Lords as the defence spokesman. He is survived by his wife April and three children. David William George Chidgey, Baron Chidgey, born July 9, 1942 died February 15, 2022